Pet Shop Boys Profile

Pet Shop Boys are an English electronic pop duo, consisting of Neil Tennant (main vocals, keyboards, occasional guitar)
and Chris Lowe (keyboards, occasional vocals).

Pet Shop Boys have sold more than 50 million records worldwide and are listed as the most successful duo in UK music
history by The Guinness Book of Records. Three-time Brit Award winners and six-time Grammy nominees, since 1985
they have achieved 42 Top 30 singles and 22 Top 10 hits in the UK Singles Chart including four UK number ones:
"West End Girls" (also number one on the US Billboard Hot 100), "It's a Sin",
a remake of Wayne Carson's "Always on My Mind" and "Heart".

Other hit songs include a remake of The Village People's "Go West", "Opportunities (Let's Make Lots of Money)"
(satire of Thatcherism which exemplified them as ironists) and "What Have I Done to Deserve This?" (with Dusty Springfield).
